ratings.question_text: Overall, how would you rate the workload of this course in comparison to other Yale courses you have taken?
What is your overall assessment of this course?
Do you expect to use this class for credit toward your major, or toward a pre-professional program?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would definitely recommend the course as it is manageable but challenging.

While it is a useful (and marketable) skill to have, the Yale Chinese Department has is too demanding for many students. I would recommend it to students who have a lot of free time to devote to Chinese; otherwise, I would not.
Chinese 130 is a lot of work, but that's why it sees results. Students improve so much because the Yale Chinese department is so strong and the curriculum and teaching are so great.
